<body>
<h1 style="color: #5e9ca0;">Guideline to use <span style="color: #2b2301;">WeatherApp</span></h1>

<p>WeatherApp is very small application, update and shown the information regarding the daily
    weather of city.You can get update of temperature, humidity, chance of rain, cloudy, wind speed
    daily or for next 5 days either of your current city or any bookmarked city. .&nbsp;</p>
<h3 style="color: #2e6c80;">How does the app behave and help you to get a weather update?</h3>
<h4 style="color: #2b2301;">Home Screen</h4>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Display your current city weather information at the top of view with your city name and
            cloudy</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>You can bookmarked any city either placing pin on map or search to view those cities
            weather info in future.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Listed all bookmarked cities with the remove option.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>You can see the bookmarked city weather or forecast details to click on name of city</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<h4 style="color: #2b2301;">Bookmark on Map</h4>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Just drag and put a marker on the location of the map, a bookmark popup at the bottom of
            the screen will appear.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Click on the bookmark button to save your selected city, which weather info you want to
            see in future.</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<h4 style="color: #2b2301;">Weather Screenp</h4>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>This screen will show you today weather info with cloudy, wind, temp, chance of rain and
            humidity.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>5 days forecast also will display with 3 hours interval of weather.</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<h4 style="color: #2b2301;">Setting Screen</h4>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Here you can set your preference for future view</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>You can change the unit of temperature measurement either celsius or Fahrenheit.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>You can also reset your bookmarked list by click on <strong>Reset bookmarked
            list</strong></p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> All data has been derived using<strong> http://openweathermap.org</strong>
    api</p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
</body>
</html>